Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Axar, out Rajpoot Run Out!! 1 run completed. KXIP have been bowled out for 88. Axar wanted to keep the strike and pushed Rajpoot for a non-existent second. In fact, it was Rajpoot who wanted the second. Axar worked the flatter delivery towards wide long-on, he was content with the single but upon seeing Rajpoot charge across, he relcutantly went for it, nice flat throw right next to the stumps from Southee and Mo did the rest. Rajpoot run out (Southee/Moeen Ali) 1(5)

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Andrew Tye, out Caught by Parthiv Patel!! What happened there? Looks like Tye wanted to review. But he's walking back. Not sure what happened. Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Ashwin, out Ashwin Run Out!! That's what wickets and pressure do. There was never a single in it and Ashwin wanted the run, Axar was tad late in sending him back and the skipper's dive was in vain. Nothing but a tossed up delivery which Ashwin taps to the left of cover, Axar took a step out before aborting from the run. And with Ashwin not being the swiftest he was always in trouble. Put in a desperate dive but was still short by some distance. Ashwin run out (Negi/Parthiv Patel) 0(1)

Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Finch, out Caught by Kohli!! Moeen Ali strikes. Each of Kohli's moves have paid off today. Brought in Siraj got a wicket, de Grandhomme did the same and Moeen Ali follows. Bit of air on this one and Finch is down on one knee to play the slog sweep, does not get the required elevation to clear deep mid-wicket and finds Kohli to perfection. The skipper had moved himself there after the third ball. KXIP slip further and their chances of getting a good total are gone with Finch. Finch c Kohli b Moeen Ali 26(23) [4s-1 6s-2]
